parameters:
\N<Segi>What do you mean...? I said I wanted to be alone with him.
Why are you here...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, I can't exactly leave you two completely alone in a
private room. After all, it's been a long time since you've
seen each other, right? It'd be troublesome if things got
heated and started right here, wouldn't it?
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>Don't make that face. I'm over here. You can't hear the
conversation, so relax.

\N<Zuuteruka>Listen up, okay? I'm warning you, if you try anything funny,
your husband's life is as good as gone, got it?
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>More importantly, are you ready? Your beloved husband is
about to arrive.
\N<Segi>Yuia...sama...
\N<Segi>Lord Yuia...
\N<Yuia>Segi...

\N<Segi>I wanted to see you... not just through a wall, but to
believe that the day would come when I could be held in your
arms like this.

\N<Yuia>...Me too. Even though it was through a wall, I could always
see your face on the other side in my heart.
\N<Segi>The face on the other side of the wall... my face...
\N<Yuia>...Is something wrong, Segi?

\N<Segi>No... it's just that I'm a little overwhelmed to finally
meet you.
\N<Segi>Lord Yuia, I... I...
I've always had a question on my mind.
Why did Lord Yuia and I come to this town?

Our family's arrival in this town was no coincidence. Lord
Yuia had a clear reason for coming here.

Above all, the emblem on the door found at the deepest part
of the ruins, the same as Lord Yuia's necklace... that very
existence proves Lord Yuia's clear intentions.

And the reason why even I was kept in the dark about it
until now. It's probably because... he didn't want to
involve me or Riia.

It's probably... something to do with fighting against
Ryuda.

As we prepare for our battle with Zuuteruka, it's something
I need to know...
\N<Segi>...
\N<Yuia>...

So... what I should be doing now is not rejoicing in our
reunion or speaking of love.

What I truly wish for... will not remove the obstacles that
stand before us now. It won't solve the root problem.

That's right... Meeting with just the two of us must have
been known to Lord Yuia in advance.

Knowing Lord Yuia, he must have imagined that it would be
under Zuuteruka's supervision like it is now.

If that's the case, then surely Lord Yuia must be thinking
the same as me...

In a way that Zuuteruka won't notice... now... he must be
trying to tell me something important.
So... I must not miss it.

\N<Yuia>Segi, is Riia doing well? He's not feeling anxious without
me around, is he?

\N<Segi>Eh? Oh... yes. Of course he feels lonely and anxious, but he
doesn't show it on his face.

\N<Yuia>I see... He's become a strong boy. I want to see him soon.
We have a promise to keep after all.
\N<Segi>A promise...?

\N<Yuia>Yeah, a promise between men. I promised him that he would
become the top cadet at the training grounds.

\N<Yuia>A promise between men... If he fulfills it, he must show his
"achievement" to his mother for sure.
\N<Segi>To me...?
\N<Yuia>...Yes.

\N<Segi>So... that's right. As for me, I don't need any medal of
honor for being top of the class as long as the child is
healthy.

\N<Yuia>No, we made a promise. That's why I'm sure he'll show me his
"results" when the time comes.
\N<Segi>Yes... I'm looking forward to that day.
\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Sorry to interrupt your fun, but it's about time.
\N<Yuia>...There should still be time left.

\N<Zuuteruka>Fun times fly by in the blink of an eye. Be satisfied that I
prepared this place for you, and it seems like your wife is
reaching her limit, huh?
\N<Segi>...!
\N<Yuia>What...?
\N<Segi>Don't say strange things... I'm fine.
\N<Yuia>...
\N<Zuuteruka>Well, that's how it is... Let's go, Segi.
\N<Segi>Lord Yuia...!

\N<Segi>A promise to become top cadet at the training grounds...?
That's news to me.

\N<Segi>Both Riia and Lord Yuia... Why have you kept this from me
until now...?

\N<Segi>If that comes true, it would be wonderful... but would he
really come all this way to tell me that in such a
situation...?

\N<Segi>Now that I think about it... I haven't seen Lord Yuia's
necklace for quite some time. When did he stop wearing
it...?

\N<Segi>It's a precious item matching with the Princess Consort's...
I thought it was just stored somewhere so it wouldn't get
lost...

\N<Segi>That's right... I've thought about the same thing here
before. Why are all of us connected to Lord Yuia or the
Princess Consort still alive...?

\N<Segi>If the answer is because Zuuteruka and the others are
scheming to obtain a secret held by Lord Yuia or someone
connected to him...
\N<Segi>...
\N<Segi>Could it be...
\N<Segi>Riia will show me his "results"...?
\N<Segi>...

\N<Segi>Wait... If Riia knows something and it's a secret promise
between him and Lord Yuia.

\N<Segi>If my hypothesis is wrong, asking Riia about it could be
dangerous...

\N<Segi>So maybe Lord Yuia thought it should remain a secret between
the two of them until the time comes...

\N<Segi>...I might be overthinking it. But... I have no other
choice.
\N<Segi>Besides... I've decided to trust Lord Yuia...
